/**
 * How to Test:
 * 
 * 1. Open this file in VS Code with the Inline extension active
 * 2. Make sure a model is loaded (check status bar)
 * 3. Place cursor at the end of each comment (after the newline)
 * 4. Wait 500ms for inline suggestions to appear
 * 5. Suggestions should appear as ghost text
 * 6. Press Tab to accept, or keep typing to dismiss
 * 7. Verify the generated code matches the comment description
 * 
 * Expected Behavior:
 * - Ghost text appears automatically after typing
 * - Suggestions are contextually relevant
 * - Code is properly formatted
 * - Type annotations are included (for TypeScript)
 * - Multi-line suggestions work correctly
 * 
 * Common Issues:
 * - If no suggestions appear, check:
 *   ✓ Model is loaded (status bar shows model name)
 *   ✓ Extension is active (check output logs)
 *   ✓ Wait at least 500ms after typing
 *   ✓ Cursor is at end of line
 */
